## Severity Definitions

| Severity | Definition | SLA |
|----------|------------|-----|
| **Critical** | Wrong revenue numbers returned; data loss; security breach | Fix before any release |
| **High** | Feature completely broken; user cannot complete core flow | Fix in current sprint |
| **Medium** | Feature partially broken; workaround exists | Fix in next sprint |
| **Low** | Visual issue; minor UX problem; non-blocking | Fix when convenient |

---

## Release Checklist (Phase 1)

Before declaring Phase 1 complete:

- [ ] All unit tests pass (`pytest tests/ -v`)
- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80% on services layer
- [ ] Golden dataset test passes with exact values
- [ ] All API endpoints have integration tests (happy path + main errors)
- [ ] SQL injection test passes
- [ ] RLS test: User A cannot see User B's data
- [ ] Duplicate import test: idempotent result confirmed
- [ ] 10,000 row import completes in < 60 seconds
- [ ] NL query for "total revenue" returns value matching direct SQL count
- [ ] Empty state UI tested (no data loaded scenario)
- [ ] Error states tested (invalid file, server error, timeout)
- [ ] All Critical and High bugs resolved and verified

