## QA Tools & Commands

```bash
# Run full test suite
pytest tests/ -v --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing

# Run only unit tests
pytest tests/unit/ -v

# Run integration tests
pytest tests/integration/ -v

# Run specific test file
pytest tests/unit/services/test_excel_parser.py -v

# Check for type errors
mypy app/

# Check code style
ruff check app/

# Run golden dataset validation
pytest tests/integration/test_golden_dataset.py -v -s
```

---

## QA's Relationship with Claude Code

When Claude Code finishes implementing a feature:
1. **Read the acceptance criteria** from `docs/user-stories/`
2. **Write tests FIRST** for every acceptance criterion
3. **Run the tests** — they should fail (red)
4. **Ask Claude Code to fix** until all tests pass (green)
5. **Check edge cases** not covered in the acceptance criteria
6. **Update the release checklist** with verified items
